children.name: Text
children.value: There's dancing in the barn from dawn 'til dusk!

children.name: Text
children.value: This place means the world to my lot!

children.name: Text
children.value: Don't let it go to ash!

children.name: Text
children.value: Scarecrow can't do owt about plague...

children.name: Text
children.value: None of me bairns better be sick!

children.name: Text
children.value: I got a bone to pick with you!

children.name: Text
children.value: Time to go against the grain!

children.name: Text
children.value: We're full o' piss and vinegar!

children.name: Text
children.value: Off today, tomorrow, and maybe the day after.

children.name: Text
children.value: I've lost the will to struggle on.

children.name: Text
children.value: I'm not sure I feel like working today.

children.name: Text
children.value: I'd not step out of line, unless it were needed.

children.name: Text
children.value: Time for a nap in the hay.

children.name: Text
children.value: Thought machines had stole me job!

children.name: Text
children.value: Thought I was off to the workhouse!

children.name: Text
children.value: We put our love into this.

children.name: Text
children.value: You keep us on our toes, master.

children.name: Text
children.value: What to do with free time!

children.name: Text
children.value: Not much left to do today.

children.name: Text
children.value: Dry hay'll only stoke the blaze!

children.name: Text
children.value: Wake me up when you're ready!

children.name: Text
children.value: Land ain't right for farmin' that.

children.name: Text
children.value: No fertility of that sort there.

children.name: Text
children.value: Peddlers say there's nowhere to take it!

children.name: Text
children.value: You needs a warehouse, you do!

children.name: Text
children.value: I likes to sing while I works.

children.name: Text
children.value: If there's no-one else, I talk with the ladybirds.

children.name: Text
children.value: Barely noticed there's a war on.

children.name: Text
children.value: Sounds like you need a few scarecrows.

children.name: Text
children.value: Keep them foreign rabbits off our lettuce!

children.name: Text
children.value: I found a sheep skull, is it a sign?

children.name: Text
children.value: Our way o' life's under threat.

children.name: Text
children.value: Candlepower ain't enough for this job.

children.name: Text
children.value: This place needs jolting into life!

children.name: Text
children.value: We're scrapin' the bottom of the barrel.

children.name: Text
children.value: Some sort o' blight on us!

children.name: Text
children.value: Here's a little summat, don't mention it.

children.name: Text
children.value: Honest work, that's all we ask.

children.name: Text
children.value: You can't treat us like this!

children.name: Text
children.value: Hear the plea of the multitude!

children.name: Text
children.value: A matter o' time before we explode!

children.name: Text
children.value: Petitions and signat'ries is all we need.

children.name: Text
children.value: I'm thinkin' of joining the chartists!

children.name: Text
children.value: If you don't listen, things are gonna get dangerous!

children.name: Text
children.value: Oh, I'm very conscious of my class!

children.name: Text
children.value: I'm unhappy, she's unhappy, we're all unhappy.

children.name: Text
children.value: You, want to know how I feel?

children.name: Text
children.value: Conditions are verging on the inhumane.

children.name: Text
children.value: Day follow day o' dreary drudge.

children.name: Text
children.value: I need something to blunt my rage on.

children.name: Text
children.value: I hear talk of the privileged.

children.name: Text
children.value: Looks fair, but there's mold in the walls.

children.name: Text
children.value: I have the hump half the time.

children.name: Text
children.value: It's all how you're born, innit?

children.name: Text
children.value: Boredom turns you onto the bad stuff.

children.name: Text
children.value: Not much in the way of common dignity.

children.name: Text
children.value: A few murmurings down the union.

children.name: Text
children.value: We'll notify yer, when we're unhappy.

children.name: Text
children.value: We look out for each other here.

children.name: Text
children.value: You can boss me around all you like.

children.name: Text
children.value: Wish I 'ad summat to complain about…

children.name: Text
children.value: Got a lovely bit o' stuff comin' in.

children.name: Text
children.value: Happy as I ever am, believe me.

children.name: Text
children.value: Who needs unions; this place is the onions.

children.name: Text
children.value: Revolution? Nahhhh. We're havin' a riot!

children.name: Text
children.value: Drunk as lords, drunk on life.

children.name: Text
children.value: If it's arson, it wasn't me!

children.name: Text
children.value: Clearly no air in our slum!

children.name: Text
children.value: I can't work if I'm sick!

children.name: Text
children.value: Always us, last to the doctor.

children.name: Text
children.value: Bayonet's not long enough to stick a hundred!

children.name: Text
children.value: We don't need them, they need us!

children.name: Text
children.value: We've the right to honest protest.

children.name: Text
children.value: Injury to one is injury to all.

children.name: Text
children.value: We've nowt to lose but our chains.

children.name: Text
children.value: Taking a break, like you said we could.

children.name: Text
children.value: If it's a lockout, we've a right to know the dispute.

children.name: Text
children.value: Some scab broke closure did they?

children.name: Text
children.value: Stand to attention for the boss!

children.name: Text
children.value: Hide the bottle, it's the boss.

children.name: Text
children.value: I even see a smidge o' daylight now!

children.name: Text
children.value: When hours are this kind, I don't ask questions.

children.name: Text
children.value: Glad I ain't up the chimminey!

children.name: Text
children.value: The workhouse a place o' plague!

children.name: Text
children.value: What kind o' town don't have a ware'ouse.

children.name: Text
children.value: Where do we take the stuff without a warehouse?

children.name: Text
children.value: We can't shut the storeroom door!

children.name: Text
children.value: I hear lack o' storage affects all the factories!

children.name: Text
children.value: They're lucky I need this job.

children.name: Text
children.value: Saves trouble, if I do exactly as I'm told.

children.name: Text
children.value: If war is what it takes!

children.name: Text
children.value: You'd hardly call it a war yet.

children.name: Text
children.value: A civilian can voice his support.

children.name: Text
children.value: Oi! Who turned off the lights?

children.name: Text
children.value: It's a right old bag o' nails.

children.name: Text
children.value: If nothing works, might as well have stayed at home.

children.name: Text
children.value: I won't be the scapegoat for this.

children.name: Text
children.value: There's a whoppin' spanner in the works.

children.name: Text
children.value: If this place were a racehorse, you'd shoot it.

children.name: Text
children.value: Take it before I change my mind.

children.name: Text
children.value: I'd never a' put ha'penny on it!

children.name: Text
children.value: Scooped us out the gutter, you did.

children.name: Text
children.value: You ain't half good to us.

children.name: Text
children.value: You've got our interests at heart.

children.name: Text
children.value: We'll raise a glass to you, guv.

children.name: Text
children.value: We're ready to break some glass.

children.name: Text
children.value: Don't think we'll play the sheep.

children.name: Text
children.value: Lording it over the working class?

children.name: Text
children.value: Pamphlets, pickets, healthy, honest protest. If some silver-spoon stiffs wants to deny us that, we'll take them shiny spoons and shove 'em...

children.name: Text
children.value: Digs is full o' kids. More likely find me out and about of an evening, seeing what's what.

children.name: Text
children.value: No harm in a bit of fun, a bit of filth. Keeps the oil lit, when work's waned yer wick.

children.name: Text
children.value: New unionism's is our future. Us filings swept into an iron tide. The rattle of the workers! Freedom and equality for all!

children.name: Text
children.value: My folks were farmers. Stink o' manure or stink o' grease, makes no odds so long as you're paid.

children.name: Text
children.value: I'll do ten of what a namby-pamby artisan do a day. Moany bourgeois milksops.

children.name: Text
children.value: I respects Engineers, right bobbish with the machines. Never know what bit of me's getting chewed up next!

children.name: Text
children.value: Investors? Crushing youth in the jaws of their machines? Trading on us like goods? Makes my bloody blood boil!

children.name: Text
children.value: Help us out, won't ya boss?

children.name: Text
children.value: Far be it from us to make the foreman work...

children.name: Text
children.value: I'm only a cog, it's you what pulls the levers.

children.name: Text
children.value: Another ten years off my life.

children.name: Text
children.value: You hoity-toities are all the same.

children.name: Text
children.value: A little love's all we ever wanted.

children.name: Text
children.value: Not bad for a big boss!

children.name: Text
children.value: Chin up boss, we ain't finished.

children.name: Text
children.value: Are we to be looked over?

children.name: Text
children.value: Haven't you ever wanted help, guv?

children.name: Text
children.value: I'm never afraid to ask twice!

children.name: Text
children.value: These are good times, could they even be better?

children.name: Text
children.value: I'm happy as sandboy, will you build us another castle?

children.name: Text
children.value: Will you work your magic for us, what we do so love to see?

children.name: Text
children.value: All we're asking for is protection!

children.name: Text
children.value: We have a right to marine safety!

children.name: Text
children.value: Can you guarantee our safe passage?

children.name: Text
children.value: What a time to be alive!

children.name: Text
children.value: Hail to thee, high above the rest!

children.name: Text
children.value: What a happy vision of yours!

children.name: Text
children.value: Drowned in the brook, rue buds in hand.

children.name: Text
children.value: Shapeless horrors climb from your abyss.

children.name: Text
children.value: Offer me not a poison chalice!

children.name: Text
children.value: My work is the love of my life, instinct over thought. You could even call it art!

children.name: Text
children.value: The truest work of art is but a shadow of its friend in nature.

children.name: Text
children.value: Someone once told me they didn't like my work, I threw myself in a nettle patch.

children.name: Text
children.value: I hope I'm not too caught-up to remember to eat once in a while!

children.name: Text
children.value: Investors enjoy the fruits of my labour, but I wonder if they know much of the tree.

children.name: Text
children.value: Engineers deride art. But true beauty lies not in things seen, but those unseen.

children.name: Text
children.value: Pity the workers! When I think of their dreary struggle, I know how fortunate I am.

children.name: Text
children.value: A farmer's life may be humblest. But green pastures, hands swept through corn, that is God's idyll!

children.name: Text
children.value: Carts do not love long grass as we do.

children.name: Text
children.value: A road would be the classical choice.

children.name: Text
children.value: Save me from this tortuous perplexity?

children.name: Text
children.value: Can any friend lift this daemon cloud?

children.name: Text
children.value: I fear my plea shan't be heard above common tumult.

children.name: Text
children.value: Even with aid, I fear it shall not be enough.

children.name: Text
children.value: I do not merit this kindness.

children.name: Text
children.value: It is I who have failed.

children.name: Text
children.value: Fate poureth poison in mine ear.

children.name: Text
children.value: Then none shall temper this torment.

children.name: Text
children.value: Then I must to my work, it is all I have.

children.name: Text
children.value: That one briefly cared, should mean something.

children.name: Text
children.value: You bring meaning to my existence?

children.name: Text
children.value: You wield the torch of hope?

children.name: Text
children.value: I see a fleeting figure upon the hill!

children.name: Text
children.value: Wild abandon courses through every limb!

children.name: Text
children.value: We have cause for urgent celebration!

children.name: Text
children.value: You do so much, dare I ask again?

children.name: Text
children.value: I'd be full of cheer, were not fresh malady upon me ...

children.name: Text
children.value: Might another barren cherry be brought to blossom?

children.name: Text
children.value: Choose not the rich, but the beautiful.

children.name: Text
children.value: Believe in more than the obvious!

children.name: Text
children.value: Might I one day be remembered...

children.name: Text
children.value: Oh for a chance of some companion ship…?

children.name: Text
children.value: I have long dreamt of caravans.

children.name: Text
children.value: Does a heavenly cortege precede us?

children.name: Text
children.value: From this bright moon, I am yet greedy for starlight!

children.name: Text
children.value: A victim of my own satisfaction, I fear I become "entitled".

children.name: Text
children.value: This must appear ungrateful, what with all I have already.

children.name: Text
children.value: All I ever desired was a place to live and work!

children.name: Text
children.value: Once bright blossom now rotting stench!

children.name: Text
children.value: I care not even for my craft.

children.name: Text
children.value: Despair, may it all end soon.

children.name: Text
children.value: My soul to the devil, or anyone!

children.name: Text
children.value: If god exists, he is too cruel!

children.name: Text
children.value: Piteous hole, a sickness of the soul.

children.name: Text
children.value: All of my life, for nothing!

children.name: Text
children.value: Like Persephone, I count my days in hell.

children.name: Text
children.value: Glum meadows, whose droop-head flowers lament.

children.name: Text
children.value: A dead pool yearning for some spawn of hope.

children.name: Text
children.value: I weep and weep as the willow.

children.name: Text
children.value: I would gladly drown among the reeds.

children.name: Text
children.value: I'd grasp a wild swan, and fly where'er it flew.

children.name: Text
children.value: I hold no hope of tomorrows.

children.name: Text
children.value: My ambitions exist mainly in the imagination!

children.name: Text
children.value: I see-saw between have and have-not.

children.name: Text
children.value: An aviary is fine, when it look not over forest.

children.name: Text
children.value: Is it wrong to want more?

children.name: Text
children.value: It's shallow, but some luxury wouldn't hurt.

children.name: Text
children.value: Life is like sea-water, that only deepens one's thirst.

children.name: Text
children.value: Full of gladness, I make my best work!

children.name: Text
children.value: I soar in heaven's bright chariot.

children.name: Text
children.value: I feel nought but a ragged joy.

children.name: Text
children.value: In this gentle bough, am I quite content.

children.name: Text
children.value: Happy melodies spring from the lyre!

children.name: Text
children.value: My soul has leave to express itself.

children.name: Text
children.value: A floodplain awash with milk and honey!

children.name: Text
children.value: This glittering carousel dizzies me, as I ascend!

children.name: Text
children.value: Euphoria! I am possessed by the demons of ecstasy!
